Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
BE A PART OF THE GROWING COMMUNITY OF BOYD LAKE VILLAGE.
Four lots are available along the US Highway 34 corridor. Boyd Lake Village
is extremely well located with visibility to state Highway 34 with convenient
access to I-25. The strong roster of retail shops and restaurants in Centerra
and across the street provide proximity to an abundance of amenities.
Current traffic counts on Eisenhower Blvd based on the 2018 CDOT traffic
data are 50,000 VPD, and I-25 has 86,000 VPD. Boyd Lake Village has three
lots with East Eisenhower Blvd frontage that benefits from the high traffic
volume and visibility. Mountain View High School is located to the south of
Eisenhower Blvd, with 1,250 students and an additional 60 staff and faculty
members.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: High Visibility Lots Available Fronting Eisenhower Blvd

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Sales Price of $6.8 million is the minimum offer acceptable
In Annexation process with the City of Loveland
Proposed Zoning Mix - Approx 156 acres R1-Residential and Approx 64 acres ER-Estate Residential

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Located just 46 miles north of Denver on the 1-25 corridor, Loveland, Colorado has something for everyone. From musical concerts, art shows and theater productions to professional hockey games, community celebrations and endless outdoor activities from hiking to biking, this is the perfect setting for a Unique Residential Development!

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: This 204+ acre residential development site is located in beautiful Loveland, an ideal location nestled in the heart of northern Colorado against the foothills of the Rocky Mountains. This property offers the potential to develop a one-of-a-kind residential development. A developer with vision, would be able to create a “legacy project” for this land. This “clean canvas” with its panoramic views and lake offers a-once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to create a special place to benefit families for generations to come!

Price: $550,000
Price Per SF: $10.48
Lot Size: 52,470 SF
Zoning: C- Commercial (Larimer County)
VPD: S Lincoln Ave.19,900

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
These sites are ideally situated at the intersection of US 34 and Cascade Avenue. Loveland, a town of 77,000, is the gateway to Northern Colorado just 10 minutes from Fort Collins and 30 minutes from beautiful Estes Park.

With abundant commuter and tourist traffic, the traffic counts surpass 14,000 VPD.
